{
  "text": "Hypoplastic left heart syndrome (HLHS) and anomalous left coronary artery from the pulmonary artery (ALCAPA) are each rare cardiovascular anomalies infrequently encountered in the same patient. A recent case series reported six patients with ALCAPA identified among 552 patients with HLHS with high mortality; a few other case reports have also documented this rare combination. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] This patient is the first documented HLHS-ALCAPA to survive all the three stages of single-ventricle palliation.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "27849619",
